g.aria-label: For Every Morning of the New Year

will this day try to live a simple sincere and serene life repelling promptly every thought of discontent, anxiety, discourage- ment, impurity and self-seek- ing cultivating cheerfulness magnanimity, charity, and the habit of holy silence exer- cising economy in expendi- ture, carefulness in conversa- tion, diligence in appointed service, fidelity to every trust and a child-like trust in God.
